    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a concours-level example of the legendary S54-powered coupe. It features the high-revving 3.2L inline-six equipped with individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing, delivering linear power delivery to an 8,000 RPM redline. The Getrag 6-speed manual transmission offers precise, short-throw gear synchronization, paired with a factory M Variable Differential Lock for exceptional lateral grip. The chassis is impeccably preserved; the rear subframe mounting points have been professionally inspected and reinforced to ensure structural rigidity. The suspension maintains its factory-spec damping rates and bushing integrity, providing the telepathic steering feedback these cars are known for. Finished in Carbon Black Metallic over Nappa leather, the cabin shows no bolster wear or UV-related degradation of the interior trim. This is a mechanically stock, turn-key specimen for the serious collector.",
      "price": 48500.0,
